sorry everybody downvoting him is just wrong wii > after the success of gekko ibm presumably grabbed this design and re branded it as ‘ cl’ for other manufacturers to use [ ] then when nintendo requested a new cpu to use with their new console still known as ‘revolution’ hence the rvl prefix on their stock motherboards ibm and nintendo agreed to use a cl clocked times the speed of gekko this cpu is known as broadway [ ] and runs at mhz > after having reviewed gekko i’m afraid there aren’t many changes found in the new cpu however this may be an advantage gamecube developers were able to start developing their new wii games right away thanks to all the experience they gained with gekko moreover the fact that broadway runs x the original speed will allow them to push for more features and quality wii u > in the end ibm grabbed three broadway cpus stepped up the clock to ghz and wrapped them with extra l cache and the necessary circuitry to arbitrate bus contention and cache coherency so it doesn’t have to be done with software that’s espresso sources the gc wii and wii u are extremely close lineage wise architecturally in a way that ryzen vs athlon aren't
